Non-GAAP Financial Measures
Debt, net of cash
Debt, net of cash is the difference between (i) the sum of long-term debt and short-term borrowings (i.e., total debt) and (ii) cash and
cash equivalents. We believe that debt, net of cash is a useful measure for investors because, as cash and cash equivalents can be
used, among other things, to repay indebtedness, netting this against total debt is a useful measure of our leverage.
